Aliyu Ibrahim, 17, has been sent to prison for one year for sodomising four boys. The National Agency for the Prohibition of Trafficking in Persons (NAPTIP) disclosed in a Facebook post that the Federal High Court 4 in Sokoto issued the verdict. “The Federal High Court 4, Sokoto state presided over by Honorable Justice Isah Muhammad Bargaja on the 23rd of January 2022 convicted Aliyu Ibrahim of rape,” the agency said. “The convict – a 17-year-old male was charged on six count charges for rape (sodomy) of four (male) victims and sentenced to one-year imprisonment without the option of fine.” 